shortAnswerSubmission.answer: Cell theory tells us that living things can only come from other living things. In 1859 Pasteur he conducted experiments proving that spontaneous generation does not exist. He used meat broth and put them into flasks and waited a few day to see how microbes were living inside the broth. Since one of his experiments was a closed lid with meat broth and one without he came to the conclusion that when the air was exposed the organisms flew inside the broth. Cell theory proved that living things can only come from other living things and not non living things.

shortAnswerSubmission.answer: The continental drift is one of the slowest things ever. Plates on the coastlines are in motion in different directions. But the movement is very slow so we barely notice it. When two plates meet the boundaries they are called divergent, convergent, and or a transform boundary. Divergent boundaries are when two plates move in opposite direction.
